5:
Those explosions definitely came
from this direction.
20:
Let go of me! Please! I have to save
Arum!
24:
Nice of you guys to show up. The
kid's being controlled somehow... I
could really use a hand bringing her
to heel.
26: Shirley, can you create an opening?
31:
Of course I can. Who do you think I
am?
35:
...And don't call me Shirley! That is
not my name!
40:
Eh, I kind of like it. Friends give each
other nicknames, right?
43:
I'm going to seal her movements.
Once I do, you're up, Arly.
46:
Guess it's time for me to get serious
for once. Let's do this.
76:
Arum, get ahold of yourself! Wake
up...
94: I've had enough of your meddling!
97: Was that the roar of a dragon?!
102:
Arum, use the shadows! Get us out
of here!
116:
He's gone... I can't believe I let him
get away...
121:
You. You used the light magic of
priests. You're an Oxtan, aren't you?
125:
Why have you betrayed the
Farlands and caused such
devastation?
128:
And who was the man that slipped
away? Answer me!
131:
Y-you've got the wrong idea. He
tricked me!
133: That was the Star Augur Procheon.
136:
He was one of the priests I once
served...
139:
And one of the people who made
me the oracle.
143: Wait, if that's the case... That means...
149: Somehow, he also knew about Arum.
152: He'll pay for this... But, I... What do I...
156:
If you're looking for where
Procheon's gone, I can show you!
160:
It just so happens I'm acquainted
with the fellow.
162:
Haha, those are quite the glares.
Why don't you give me the chance
to explain first?
166:
I swear, I haven't betrayed you! I
know how it looks, but I promise I'm
on your side this time!
